  "review_text": "[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=extralarge; fonttype=bold; text=The Scenario]\n\n[SPAN: fontsize=larger; fonttype=italic; text=You built a time machine to study Marvel history up close.]\n[BR] [SPAN: fontsize=larger; fonttype=italic; text= It] [SPAN: severity=error; fontsize=larger; fonttype=italic; text=exploded] [SPAN: fontsize=larger; fonttype=italic; text=the moment you arrived.]\n[BR]\n[ASSET: center | TimeMachineExplosion | width=50%]\n\nOne second you were in your own century.&nbsp; The next, you were standing in <b>1961</b>, surrounded by only a stack of fresh comics, confused editors, the faint smell of newsprint, and the hope that reading forward -- one month at a time -- will eventually return you to the present (unless someone in 1961 invents a better time-travel device -- and unless you're Victor Von Doom, <i>that's not happening</i>).\n\nThe machine is [SPAN: severity=error; fonttype=bold; text=gone].\n[BR]The future is out of reach.\n[BR]And the only way forward... is... [SPAN: fontsize=small; fonttype=italic; text=well...] <b>forward</b>.\n\n[SPAN: severity=info; fonttype=bold; text=This is the Scenario:]\n[BR] [HANG] A long-form, slow-motion reconstruction of the Marvel Universe, lived in real time from the moment it begins.\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Where You Are]\n\nYou're standing at the spinner rack in a world where:\n[HANG] * The Fantastic Four have only <i>just</i> appeared\n[HANG] * Spider-Man doesn't exist yet\n[HANG] * \"Mutant\" is a word, <i>sure</i> -- but the Marvel kind is still almost two years from now\n[HANG] * The Marvel Universe is a fragile experiment that might collapse at any moment\n\nEvery issue is [SPAN: severity=success; fonttype=bold; text=new].\n[BR] Every character is [SPAN: severity=error; fonttype=bold; text=untested].\n[BR] Every creative choice is a [SPAN: severity=warning; fonttype=bold; text=gamble].\n\nYou <i>know</i> what Marvel will eventually become - but you can't jump ahead to it.&nbsp; [SPAN: fontsize=small; text=(Your time machine made sure of that.)]\n[BR] You have only your vague \"future memories\" available -- and no way to verify anything, so it's best to stick to what's on the page.\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Why You're Here]\n\nBecause the only way to understand Marvel's strange, sprawling, physics-optional evolution is to <b>experience it in real time</b>, with all the awkwardness, brilliance, repetition, invention, and accidental genius intact.\n\nThis project is built on:\n[HANG] * <b>Continuity preservation</b> -- no reboots, no shortcuts, no skipping ahead\n[HANG] * <b>Real-time reading</b> -- you're stuck moving through Marvel history at its original speed (no fast‑forward button)\n[HANG] * <b>Affectionate mockery</b> -- because even the classics need a gentle ribbing\n[HANG] * <b>Long form history</b> -- the Marvel Universe as a lived experience, not a retrospective or wiki summary\n\nYou're not just reading comics.\n[BR]You're inhabiting them (and in some cases, [SPAN: severity=warning; fonttype=bold-italic; text=surviving] them - [SPAN: fontsize=small; text=this is where it's important to laugh]).\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=How It Works]\n\nThe rules of the Scenario are simple:\n[HANG] * <b>You start in 1961</b> with <i>Fantastic Four</i> #1 [SPAN: fontsize=small; text=(more or less)]\n[HANG] * <b>You move forward chronologically</b>, month by month, <i>in publication order</i>\n[HANG] * <b>You acknowledge everything on the spinner rack</b> - <i>Patsy and Hedy</i>, <i>Millie the Model</i>, <i>Love Romances</i>, <i>Rawhide Kid</i>, <b>all</b> of it -- but you <i>note</i> it and <i>keep turning</i>.&nbsp; (This project follows the main Marvel Universe, not every side‑title.)\n[HANG] * <b>You don't use hindsight</b> -- you react as a reader of the time. [SPAN: fontsize=small; text=(Your future memories are vague and might be unreliable.)]\n[HANG] * <b>You let the Marvel Universe assemble itself around you at its original pace</b>\n\nThe goal isn't to rush to the good parts.\n[BR] [SPAN: severity=info; fonttype=bold; text=The goal is to watch the good parts <i>form</i>.]\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=What You'll Find Here]\n\n<b>Longbox Playback</b> is your guide through this time-locked journey.&nbsp; Each review is written as if grounded in the moment, but aware of the larger tapestry being woven.\n\nYou'll see:\n[HANG] * <b>Issue reviews</b> that balance gut-feel reactions with deep-dive analysis (all written from <i>within the Scenario</i>)\n[HANG] * <b>Start at-the-beginning navigation</b> for fellow stranded travelers\n[HANG] * <b>Decoder Ring insights</b> for optional meta context.&nbsp; [DECODER_RING: The extra context appears here when you hover over the ring (or click on it if your device does not support hover events)!] (see details [PAGE: decoder-ring | here])\n[HANG] * <b>Vintage Moment Awards</b>, because some panels deserve a trophy [SPAN: fontsize=small; fonttype=italic; text=(or a double-take!)]\n\nYou're not alone in the past -- you're part of a reading expedition.\n[BR] This is a shared time capsule adventure in a world [SPAN: severity=info; fonttype=bold; text=that doesn't know it's historic yet].\n\n[DIVIDER]\n[SPAN: display=block; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=Your Role in the Scenario]\n\nYou're the traveler.\n[BR]The witness.\n[BR] The person who remembers the future... but can't reach it.\n\nYour job is simple:\n[HANG] Read forward.\n[HANG] Stay in the moment.\n[HANG] Let the universe assemble itself around you.\n\nAnd when you're ready, step into the first month and press... [SPAN: severity=info; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=PLAY]\n[BR] [SPAN: severity=success; fontsize=larger; fonttype=bold; text=Good luck!]"
}